        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support z.ai BigModel team usage",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- Support z.ai BigModel team usage through saved token accounts in Settings, CLI, and config using `usageScope: team`, `organizationId`, and `workspaceID`.\r\n- Route z.ai team quota/model/hourly requests with the BigModel team selectors and headers while personal accounts clear team context.\r\n- Add `codexbar config set-api-key --provider zai ... --usage-scope team ...` plus focused CLI/config tests.\r\n- Keep z.ai docs concise and add missing localized labels for Team mode / Organization ID.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\nBigModel team Coding Plan usage can return empty personal data unless queried with the team selector and BigModel organization/project headers. The token-account path supports personal and team z.ai accounts without adding browser-cookie auth or a global `Z_AI_USAGE_SCOPE` setting.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- z.ai team scope is account-level only; `Z_AI_USAGE_SCOPE` is not read or documented.\r\n- Team accounts require single-line BigModel organization and project IDs.\r\n- Existing legacy z.ai Keychain token migration remains only for old API-token storage migration.\r\n\r\n## Screenshots/GIFs\r\n- Not included: visible changes are limited to Settings token-account fields/labels and are covered by descriptor/localization tests.\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n- `swift test --filter CLIConfigCommandTests`\r\n- `swift test --filter LocalizationLanguageCatalogTests`\r\n- `make check`\r\n- `make test`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n\r\n\r\n<img width=\"306\" height=\"505\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3ed6e249-fae6-4d26-996a-64ef561483c8\" />\r\n<img width=\"530\" height=\"632\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93aae4d9-ef9e-45a8-8a58-052c6b182909\" />\r\n",
